<recipe>
    <name>Thai Beef and Spinach Stir Fry</name>
    <indexCharacter>T</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Heat the wok on high sear setting, add 1 tablespoon oil and stir fry the garlic, ginger and onions. Cook for 2 minutes. Then add the red peppers. Cook for 2 minutes more, then remove.

2. Add the remaining tablespoon of oil and stir fry the beef in small batches for 1 - 2 minutes.

3. Remove when cooked and allow wok to reheat before stir frying next batch.

4. Return all the ingredients to the wok.

5. Reduce to a medium heat, setting 8, until spinach has softened.

Serve with coconut rice.</instructions>
